This has a more elementary proof that belongs in another file:

```lean
lemma norm_nsmul [NormedAddCommGroup E] [NormedSpace ℝ E] (n : ℕ) (x : E) : ‖n • x‖ = n • ‖x‖ := by
  rw [nsmul_eq_smul_cast ℝ, norm_smul, IsROrC.norm_natCast, nsmul_eq_mul]
```
or even
```lean
lemma norm_nsmul [IsROrC 𝕜] [NormedAddCommGroup E] [NormedSpace 𝕜 E] (n : ℕ) (x : E) : ‖n • x‖ = n • ‖x‖ := by
  rw [nsmul_eq_smul_cast 𝕜, norm_smul, IsROrC.norm_natCast, nsmul_eq_mul]
```
next to `IsROrC.norm_natCast`.
Nice!
Please make `K` explicit in this formula. It doesn't appear on either side of the formula.
Assume `IsScalarTower S R M` and something like `OrderedSMul S R`? Will it work?

```suggestion
lemma _root_.SameRay.nsmul_right (v : M) (n : ℕ) : SameRay R v (n • v) := by
```
for `(.nsmul_right _ _)` notation.
Oh nevermind, I see this conflicts with below.
I'd lean towards removing these, and forcing the user to write `refl.nsmul_right` or whatever.

What about the similar ones for `smul` by `R` that already exist?

PS: Those conflicts, I think, are a pretty fundamental flaw of this new `(.bar _)` notation wrt our naming convention.
Should it be `gcongr` as well?
Could you please add a `positivity` extension for `algebraMap` using this lemma and `algebraMap_pos` below?

I'm not managing to pattern-match on `algebraMap` because of the `FunLike.coe`. Here's my attempt. I won't have more time to spend on making this work.
```lean
namespace Mathlib.Meta.Positivity
open Lean Meta Qq Function

/-- Extension for `algebraMap`. -/
@[positivity algebraMap _ _ _]
def evalAlgebraMap : PositivityExt where eval {u α} _zα _pα e := do
  let ~q(@FunLike.coe _ _ _ _ (@algebraMap $α $β $instα $instβ $instαβ) $a) := e | throwError "not algebraMap"
  -- let zα' : Q(Zero ℚ) := q(inferInstance)
  -- let pα' : Q(PartialOrder ℚ) := q(inferInstance)
  -- match ← core zα' pα' a with
  -- | .positive pa =>
  --   let _oα ← synthInstanceQ (q(LinearOrderedField $α) : Q(Type u))
  --   pure (.positive (q((Rat.cast_pos (K := $α)).mpr $pa) : Expr))
  -- | .nonnegative pa =>
  --   let _oα ← synthInstanceQ (q(LinearOrderedField $α) : Q(Type u))
  --   pure (.nonnegative (q((Rat.cast_nonneg (K := $α)).mpr $pa) : Expr))
  -- | .nonzero pa =>
  --   let _oα ← synthInstanceQ (q(DivisionRing $α) : Q(Type u))
  --   let _cα ← synthInstanceQ (q(CharZero $α) : Q(Prop))
  --   pure (.nonzero (q((Rat.cast_ne_zero (α := $α)).mpr $pa) : Expr))
  -- | .none => pure .none


example [OrderedSemiring β] [Algebra α β] [SMulPosMono α β] {a : α} (ha : 0 ≤ a) :
    0 ≤ algebraMap α β a := by positivity
```

A regular match works fine:
```
@[positivity algebraMap _ _ _]
def evalAlgebraMap : PositivityExt where eval {u β'} _zβ _pβ e := do
  let ~q(@algebraMap $α _ $instα $instβ $instαβ $a) := e | throwError "not algebraMap"
  let zα : Q(Zero $α) := q(inferInstance)
  let (pα' : Q(PartialOrder $α)) ← synthInstanceQ _
  sorry
```
though I haven't tried to write the rest.
Please add a version with unfolded definition and make it `@[mono, gcongr]` (`mono` can accept `Monotone` lemmas while `gcongr` can't).
Same as above about `mono` and `gcongr`.
